# AC Waveform and AC Circuit Theory  交流波形与交流电路理论

AC Sinusoidal Waveforms are created by rotating a coil within a magnetic field and alternating voltages and currents form the basis of AC Theory  
交流正弦波形是通过在磁场内旋转线圈产生的，交流电压和电流构成了交流理论的基础。

The AC waveform used the most in circuit theory is that of the sinusoidal waveform or sine wave.  
在电路理论中最常用的交流波形是正弦波形。

A periodic AC waveform in the form of a voltage source produces an EMF whose polarity reverses at regular intervals with the time required to complete one full reversal being known as the waveforms period.  
以电压源形式的周期性交流波形产生电动势，其极性会定期反转，完成一次完整反转所需的时间称为波形的周期。

**Direct Current** or **D.C.** as it is more commonly called, is a form of electrical current or voltage that flows around an electrical circuit in one direction only, making it a “Uni-directional” supply.  
直流电，通常称为D.C.，是一种电流或电压形式，在电路中仅沿一个方向流动，因此是一种“单向”的电源。

Generally, both DC currents and voltages are produced by power supplies, batteries, dynamos and solar cells to name a few.  
通常，直流电流和电压由电源、蓄电池、发电机和太阳能电池等产生。

A DC voltage or current has a fixed magnitude (amplitude) and a definite direction associated with it.  
直流电压或电流具有固定的幅值（振幅）和确定的方向。

For example, $+12V$ represents 12 volts in the positive direction, or $-5V$ represents 5 volts in the negative direction.  
例如，+12V 表示正向的12伏，-5V 表示负向的5伏。

We also know that DC power supplies do not change their value with regards to time, they are a constant value flowing in a continuous steady state direction.  
我们还知道，直流电源的电压值随时间不变，它们是以连续稳定的状态沿一个方向流动的常数值。

In other words, DC maintains the same value for all times and a constant uni-directional DC supply never changes or becomes negative unless its connections are physically reversed.  
换句话说，直流电始终保持恒定的值，且一个恒定的单向直流电源不会变化或变为负值，除非其接线方向被物理反转。

An example of a simple DC or direct current circuit is shown below.  
下面展示了一个简单的直流电路示例。
### DC Circuit and Waveform 直流电路和波形  
<p align="center"><img src="https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/accircuits-acp1.gif" alt="DC circuit and waveform"/></p>  

An alternating function or **AC Waveform** on the other hand is defined as one that varies in both magnitude and direction in more or less an even manner with respect to time making it a “Bi-directional” waveform.  
另一方面，交流函数或**交流波形**被定义为一种幅度和方向都会随时间以或多或少均匀的方式变化的波形，使其成为“双向”波形。  

An AC function can represent either a power source or a signal source with the shape of an _AC waveform_ generally following that of a mathematical sinusoid being defined as: $A(t) = A_{max} * \sin(2\pi ft)$ .  
交流函数可以表示电源或信号源，交流波形的形状通常遵循数学上的正弦函数，定义为：$A(t) = A_{max} * \sin(2\pi ft)$ 。  

The term AC or to give it its full description of Alternating Current, generally refers to a time-varying waveform with the most common of all being called a **Sinusoid** better known as a **Sinusoidal Waveform** .  
“交流”或其全称“交流电”通常指的是一种随时间变化的波形，其中最常见的被称为**正弦波**，更准确地说是**正弦波形**。  

Sinusoidal waveforms are more generally called by their short description as **Sine Waves** .  
正弦波形通常简称为**正弦波**。  

Sine waves are by far one of the most important types of AC waveform used in electrical engineering.  
正弦波无疑是电气工程中最重要的交流波形类型之一。  

The shape obtained by plotting the instantaneous ordinate values of either voltage or current against time is called an **AC Waveform** .  
将电压或电流的瞬时纵坐标值随时间绘制出的图形称为**交流波形**。  

An AC waveform is constantly changing its polarity every half cycle alternating between a positive maximum value and a negative maximum value respectively with regards to time with a common example of this being the domestic mains voltage supply we use in our homes.  
交流波形每半个周期就不断改变其极性，依次交替在正最大值和负最大值之间变化，时间上呈现这样的变化，家用市电电压即为一个常见例子。  

This means then that the _AC Waveform_ is a “time-dependent signal” with the most common type of time-dependant signal being that of the **Periodic Waveform** .  
这意味着交流波形是一种“时间依赖信号”，其中最常见的时间依赖信号类型是**周期波形**。  

The periodic or AC waveform is the resulting product of a rotating electrical generator.  
周期波形或交流波形是旋转电机产生的结果。  

Generally, the shape of any periodic waveform can be generated using a fundamental frequency and superimposing it with harmonic signals of varying frequencies and amplitudes but that’s for another tutorial.  
一般来说，任何周期波形的形状都可以通过基频叠加不同频率和幅度的谐波信号来产生，但这将在另一个教程中讲解。  

Alternating voltages and currents can not be stored in batteries or cells like direct current (DC) can, it is much easier and cheaper to generate these quantities using alternators or waveform generators when they are needed.  
交流电压和电流不能像直流电那样存储在电池或电池组中，当需要时，使用交流发电机或波形发生器生成这些量要更容易且成本更低。  

The type and shape of an AC waveform depends upon the generator or device producing them, but all AC waveforms consist of a zero voltage line that divides the waveform into two symmetrical halves.  
交流波形的类型和形状取决于产生它们的发电机或设备，但所有交流波形都包含一条零电压线，将波形分成两个对称的半部。  

The main characteristics of an **AC Waveform** are defined as:  
**交流波形**的主要特性定义为：
### AC Waveform Characteristics 交流波形特性

* $T$ is the length of time in seconds that the waveform takes to repeat itself from start to finish.  
$T$ 是指波形从开始到结束自身重复一次所需的时间，单位为秒。

This can also be called the _Periodic Time_ of the waveform for sine waves, or the _Pulse Width_ for square waves.  
对于正弦波，这也可称为波形的_周期_，对于方波，则称为_脉冲宽度_。

* $The Frequency, (f)$ is the number of times the waveform repeats itself within a one second time period.  
$频率(f)$ 是指波形在一秒钟时间内自身重复的次数。

Frequency is the reciprocal of the time period, ( $ƒ = 1/T$ ) with the unit of frequency being the _ Hertz_ , (Hz).  
频率是周期的倒数（$ƒ = 1/T$），其单位为_赫兹_（Hz）。

* $The Amplitude (A)$ is the magnitude or intensity of the signal waveform measured in volts or amps.  
$幅值(A)$ 为信号波形的大小或强度，以伏特或安培为单位进行测量。

In our tutorial about [ Waveforms ](https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/waveforms/waveforms.html) ,we looked at different types of waveforms and said that “ **Waveforms** are basically a visual representation of the variation of a voltage or current plotted to a base of time”.  
在我们关于[波形](https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/waveforms/waveforms.html)的教程中，我们查看了不同类型的波形，并指出：“**波形**本质上是将电压或电流的变化相对于时间进行可视化表现。”

Generally, for AC waveforms this horizontal base line represents a zero condition of either voltage or current.  
通常，对于交流波形，这条水平基线表示电压或电流的零状态。

Any part of an AC type waveform which lies above the horizontal zero axis represents a voltage or current flowing in one direction.  
交流型波形中位于水平零轴之上的任何部分表示电压或电流沿一个方向流动。

Likewise, any part of the waveform which lies below the horizontal zero axis represents a voltage or current flowing in the opposite direction to the first.  
同样，波形中位于水平零轴以下的任何部分表示电压或电流沿相反方向流动。

Generally for sinusoidal AC waveforms the shape of the waveform above the zero axis is the same as the shape below it.  
一般来说，对于正弦交流波形，零轴以上部分的波形与零轴以下部分的波形形状相同。

However, for most non-power AC signals including audio waveforms this is not always the case.  
然而，对于大多数非电力交流信号（包括音频波形）来说，情况并非总是如此。

The most common periodic signal waveforms that are used in Electrical and Electronic Engineering are the _Sinusoidal Waveforms_ .  
在电气和电子工程中最常用的周期性信号波形是_正弦波形_。

However, an alternating AC waveform may not always take the shape of a smooth shape based around the trigonometric sine or cosine function.  
然而，交流波形并不总是取基于三角正弦或余弦函数的平滑形状。

AC waveforms can also take the shape of either _Complex Waves_ , _Square Waves_ or _Triangular Waves_ and these are shown below.  
交流波形还可以呈现_复合波_、_方波_或_三角波_的形状，如下图所示。
### Types of Periodic Waveform 波形的周期类型

<p align="center"><img src="https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/accircuits-acp2.gif" alt="periodic AC waveform"/></p>

The time taken for an **AC Waveform** to complete one full pattern from its positive half to its negative half and back to its zero baseline again is called a **Cycle** and one complete cycle contains both a positive half-cycle and a negative half-cycle.  
交流波形从正半周到负半周再回到零基线所用的时间称为一个**周期（Cycle）**，一个完整的周期包括正半周和负半周。

The time taken by the waveform to complete one full cycle is called the **Periodic Time** of the waveform, and is given the symbol “T”.  
波形完成一个完整周期所用的时间称为波形的**周期时间（Periodic Time）**，用符号“T”表示。

The number of complete cycles that are produced within one second (cycles/second) is called the **Frequency** , symbol $ƒ$ of the alternating waveform.  
在一秒内完成的完整周期数（周期/秒）称为**频率（Frequency）**，用符号$ƒ$表示。

Frequency is measured in **Hertz** , ( $Hz$ ) named after the German physicist Heinrich Hertz.  
频率的单位是**赫兹（Hertz）**，( $Hz$ )，以德国物理学家海因里希·赫兹的名字命名。

Then we can see that a relationship exists between cycles (oscillations), periodic time and frequency (cycles per second), so if there are $ƒ$ number of cycles in one second, each individual cycle must take $1/ƒ$ seconds to complete.  
我们可以看出，周期数（振荡次数）、周期时间和频率（每秒周期数）之间存在关系，所以如果一秒钟内有$ƒ$个周期，那么每个周期所需的时间就是$1/ƒ$秒。

Frequency used to be expressed in “cycles per second” abbreviated to “cps”, but today it is more commonly specified in units called “Hertz”.  
频率以前用“每秒周数”（cycles per second，简称cps）表示，但现在更常用的单位是“赫兹”（Hertz）。

For a domestic mains supply the frequency will be either 50Hz or 60Hz depending upon the country and is fixed by the speed of rotation of the generator.  
对于家庭电网来说，频率根据国家的不同会是50Hz或60Hz，这是由发电机的转速决定的。

But one hertz is a very small unit so prefixes are used that denote the order of magnitude of the waveform at higher frequencies such as **kHz** , **MHz** and even **GHz** .  
但是1赫兹是一个很小的单位，因此在更高频率时会用前缀来表示数量级，比如**千赫兹（kHz）**、**兆赫兹（MHz）**，甚至**吉赫兹（GHz）**。

## Amplitude of an AC Waveform  交流波形的幅值

As well as knowing either the periodic time or the frequency of the alternating quantity, another important parameter of the AC waveform is **Amplitude** , better known as its Maximum or Peak value represented by the terms, $V_{max}$ for voltage or $I_{\text{max}}$ for current.  
除了了解交流量的周期时间或频率外，交流波形的另一个重要参数是**幅值**，通常也称为最大值或峰值，用$V_{max}$表示电压峰值，用$I_{\text{max}}$表示电流峰值。

The peak value is the greatest value of either voltage or current that the waveform reaches during each half cycle measured from the zero baseline.  
峰值是指波形在每个半周期内相对于零基线所达到的最大电压或电流值。

Unlike a DC voltage or current which has a steady state that can be measured or calculated using [ Ohm’s Law ](https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/dccircuits/dcp_2.html) , an alternating quantity is constantly changing its value over time.  
与可以用[欧姆定律](https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/dccircuits/dcp_2.html)测量或计算出的具有稳定状态的直流电压或电流不同，交流量的数值随着时间不断变化。

For pure sinusoidal waveforms this peak value will always be the same for both half cycles ( $+V_m = -V_m$ )  
对于纯正弦波形，这一峰值在两个半周期内恒为相同（$+V_m = -V_m$）

but for non-sinusoidal or complex waveforms the maximum peak value can be very different for each half cycle.  
但对于非正弦波形或复杂波形，每个半周期内的最大峰值可能会有很大不同。

Sometimes, alternating waveforms are given a _peak-to-peak_ , $V_{p-p}$ value and this is simply the distance or the sum in voltage between the maximum peak value, $V_{max}$ and the minimum peak value, $-V_{max}$ during one complete cycle.  
有时，交流波形会给出峰-峰值（$V_{p-p}$），它只是指在一个完整周期内，最大峰值$V_{max}$与最小峰值$-V_{max}$之间的电压距离或总和。
## The Average Value of an AC Waveform  交流波形的平均值

The average or mean value of a continuous DC voltage will always be equal to its maximum peak value as a DC voltage is constant.  
连续直流电压的平均值总是等于它的最大峰值，因为直流电压是恒定的。

This average value will only change if the duty cycle of the DC voltage changes.  
这个平均值只有在直流电压的占空比发生变化时才会改变。

In a pure sine wave if the average value is calculated over the full cycle, the average value would be equal to zero as the positive and negative halves will cancel each other out.  
对于纯正弦波，如果在整个周期内计算其平均值，平均值将等于零，因为正半周和负半周会相互抵消。

So the average or mean value of an AC waveform is calculated or measured over a half cycle only and this is shown below.  
因此，交流波形的平均值只在半个周期内进行计算或测量，下面将展示这一点。
### Average Value of a Non-sinusoidal Waveform 非正弦波形的平均值

<p align="center"><img src="https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/accircuits-acp6.gif" alt="AC waveform average value"/></p>

To find the average value of the waveform we need to calculate the area underneath the waveform using the mid-ordinate rule, trapezoidal rule or the Simpson’s rule found commonly in mathematics.  
要找到波形的平均值，我们需要用数学中常见的中纵线法、梯形法或辛普森法来计算波形下方的面积。

The approximate area under any irregular waveform can easily be found by simply using the mid-ordinate rule.  
对于任何不规则波形的近似面积，都可以很容易地用中纵线法来求出。

The zero axis base line is divided up into any number of equal parts and in our simple example above this value was nine, ($V_{1}$ to $V_{9}$).  
零轴基线被分成任意数量的等分，在我们上面的简单例子中，这个数量是九份（$V_{1}$ 到 $V_{9}$）。

The more ordinate lines that are drawn the more accurate will be the final average or mean value.  
绘制的纵线越多，最后求得的平均值就会越准确。

The average value will be the addition of all the instantaneous values added together and then divided by the total number.  
平均值就是将所有瞬时值加在一起，然后再除以总数。

其表达式为：

For a pure sinusoidal waveform this average or mean value will always be equal to $0.637 \times V_{\text{max}}$ and this relationship also holds true for average values of current.  
对于一个纯正弦波形，这个平均值（或称均值）总是等于 $0.637 \times V_{\text{max}}$，这一关系对于电流的平均值同样适用。
## The RMS Value of an AC Waveform 交流波形的均方根（RMS）值

The average value of an AC waveform that we calculated above as being: $ 0.637 \times V_{\text{max}} $ is NOT the same value we would use for a DC supply.  
我们上面计算得到的交流波形的平均值：$ 0.637 \times V_{\text{max}} $，并不是我们为直流供电时使用的相同的值。

This is because unlike a DC supply which is constant and of a fixed value, an AC waveform is constantly changing over time and has no fixed value.  
这是因为与恒定不变且固定数值的直流电源不同，交流波形会随着时间不断变化，没有固定的数值。

Thus the equivalent value for an alternating current system that provides the same amount of electrical power to a load as a DC equivalent circuit is called the “effective value”.  
因此，在交流系统中能够向负载提供与直流等效电路相同电功率的等效值被称为“有效值”。

The effective value of a sine wave produces the same $I^2R$ heating effect in a load as we would expect to see if the same load was fed by a constant DC supply.  
正弦波的有效值在负载中产生的 $I^2R$ 热效应与由恒定直流电源向同一负载供电时产生的热效应是相同的。

The effective value of a sine wave is more commonly known as the **Root Mean Squared** or simply **RMS** value as it is calculated as the square root of the mean (average) of the square of the voltage or current.  
正弦波的有效值通常被称为**均方根值**（**RMS**），因为它是通过对电压或电流的平方取平均值后，再开平方得到的。

That is $ V_{\text{rms}} $ or $ I_{\text{rms}} $ is given as the square root of the average of the sum of all the squared mid-ordinate values of the sine wave.  
也就是说，$ V_{\text{rms}} $ 或 $ I_{\text{rms}} $ 是由正弦波所有中值处的平方值的平均值再开平方而得到的。

The RMS value for any AC waveform can be found from the following modified average value formula as shown.  
任何交流波形的RMS值可以通过下述修正后的平均值公式来计算。

Where: $n$ equals the number of mid-ordinates.

For a pure sinusoidal waveform this effective or R.M.S. value will always be equal too: $1/$ $\sqrt{}$ $2$ $V_{max}$ which is equal to $0.707 \times V_{\text{max}}$ and this relationship holds true for RMS values of current.  
对于一个纯正弦波形，有效值或均方根值始终等于：$1/$ $\sqrt{}$ $2$ $V_{max}$，即等于 $0.707 \times V_{\text{max}}$，这个关系同样适用于电流的均方根值。

The RMS value for a sinusoidal waveform is always greater than the average value except for a rectangular waveform.  
除了方波以外，正弦波形的均方根值总是大于其平均值。

In this case the heating effect remains constant so the average and the RMS values will be the same.  
在这种情况下，热效应是恒定的，因此平均值和均方根值是相同的。

One final comment about R.M.S. values.  
关于均方根值的最后一点说明。

Most multimeters, either digital or analogue unless otherwise stated only measure the R.M.S. values of voltage and current and not the average.  
大多数多用电表，无论是数字的还是模拟的，除非另有说明，仅测量电压和电流的均方根值，而不是平均值。

Therefore when using a multimeter on a direct current system the reading will be equal to $I = V/R$ and for an alternating current system the reading will be equal to $I_{rms} = \frac{V_{rms}}{R}$ .  
因此，在直流系统中使用多用电表时，读数等于 $I = V/R$，而在交流系统中读数等于 $I_{rms} = \frac{V_{rms}}{R}$ 。

Also, except for average power calculations, when calculating RMS or peak voltages, only use $V_{\text{RMS}}$ to find $I_{\text{RMS}}$ values, or peak voltage, $V_p$ to find peak current, $I_p$ values.  
另外，除了平均功率计算之外，在计算均方根值或峰值电压时，只能用 $V_{\text{RMS}}$ 来求 $I_{\text{RMS}}$，或用峰值电压 $V_p$ 来求峰值电流 $I_p$。

Do not mix them together as Average, RMS or Peak values of a sine wave are completely different and your results will definitely be incorrect.  
不要把它们混在一起，因为正弦波的平均值、均方根值和峰值是完全不同的，将它们混用肯定会导致错误的结果。
## Form Factor and Crest Factor  波形因数和峰值因数  
Although little used these days, both **Form Factor** and **Crest Factor** can be used to give information about the actual shape of the AC waveform.  
虽然现在很少使用，波形因数和峰值因数都可以用来提供交流波形实际形状的信息。  

Form Factor is the ratio between the average value and the RMS value and is given as.  
波形因数是平均值与有效值的比值，其表达式为。  

<p align="center"><img src="https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/accircuits-acp9.gif" alt="AC waveform form factor"/></p>  

For a pure sinusoidal waveform the Form Factor will always be equal to $1.11$ .  
对于纯正弦波，波形因数总是等于$1.11$。  

Crest Factor is the ratio between the R.M.S. value and the Peak value of the waveform and is given as.  
峰值因数是波形的有效值与峰值的比值，其表达式为。  

<p align="center"><img src="https://www.electronics-tutorials.ws/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/accircuits-acp10.gif" alt="AC waveform crest factor"/></p>  

For a pure sinusoidal waveform the Crest Factor will always be equal to $\sqrt{2}$ .  
对于纯正弦波，峰值因数总是等于$\sqrt{2}$。
